<subSubSection id="C34065156321FFDAFF12FB09FCA1FD1F" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="468" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6321FFDBFF12FB09FAD4F9D7" blockId="16.[151,1437,1279,2025]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFF12FB09FE8CFAF7" bold="true" box="[151,267,1279,1305]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Remarks:</emphasis>
The original label has, unfortunately, been replaced by a new label (
<figureCitation id="13612A1B6321FFDBFB9AFB09FB08FAF4" box="[1055,1167,1279,1306]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,787,811]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,186,761]" captionTargetId="figure-24@16.[149,1437,181,763]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by T. Salvadori. a) Ptilotis erythropleura NHMO-BI-86778 (collector’s label); b) Melanocharis chloroptera NHMO-BI-61863 (NHMO label); c) Zosterops novae guineae NHMO-BI-86649 (NHMO label); d) Dicaeum misoriense NHMO-BI-61856 (collector’s label)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626777/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Figure 6b</figureCitation>
) after the arrival of the specimen in NHMO, and the information on this label is neither complete (e.g., no indication that the specimen is a 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6321FFDBFF12FAB1FF4DFA8F" box="[151,202,1351,1377]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">type</typeStatus>
), nor fully correct (the locality is given as 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFD27FAB1FC0BFA8F" box="[674,908,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">‘Gobia-Lengan, Aru’</emphasis>
). It does, however, include information that the specimen was received from 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFE5AFA9DFD0EFA6B" box="[479,649,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">‘Mus. Gen. 88’</emphasis>
, an annotation that all the skins received from Genoa in 1888 have in common. Further, Collett received a printed list of specimens offered by the museum in Genoa (
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFB27FA79FE3FFA23" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
‘Duplicati della 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6321FFDBFAD0FA66FF6FFA23" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Nuova" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guinea">Nuova Guinea</taxonomicName>
e delle Molucche’
</emphasis>
) together with the accompanying letter from Giacomo Doria, in which all the taxa in the shipment were ticked off (probably by Doria, based on his wording in the letter). In the list, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6321FFDBFBF8FA21FA1AFA1F" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[1149,1437,1495,1521]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFBF8FA21FA1AFA1F" box="[1149,1437,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Melanocharis chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indicated as 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFEBCFA0DFE0EF9FB" box="[313,393,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">‘tipico’</emphasis>
and also ticked off, in the same way as for 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6321FFDBFCE6FA0DFBC8F9FB" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[867,1103,1531,1557]" class="Aves" family="Meliphagidae" genus="Ptilotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythropleura">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFCE6FA0DFBC8F9FB" box="[867,1103,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Ptilotis erythropleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6321FFDBFBD8FA0AFAE9F9FB" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1878" box="[1117,1390,1532,1557]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="novae" subSpecies="guineae">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFBD8FA0AFAE9F9FB" box="[1117,1390,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Zosterops novae guineae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6321FFDBFF12F9D6FEFFF9D7" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[151,376,1568,1593]" class="Aves" family="Dicaeidae" genus="Dicaeum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="misoriense">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFF12F9D6FEFFF9D7" box="[151,376,1568,1593]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Dicaeum misoriense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It must, therefore, be concluded that this specimen is part of the 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6321FFDBFBC2F9E9FBF1F9D7" box="[1095,1142,1567,1593]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">type</typeStatus>
series of this taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6321FFDBFF42F9B5FC66F8FF" blockId="16.[151,1437,1279,2025]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
Assuming that the locality on the label refers to Giabu-lengan on the Aru Islands, and the collection date (
<date id="FFE4105E6321FFDBFAFAF9B5FE8BF96F" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="1873-05-24">24 May 1873</date>
) is correct, the specimen can be either specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFCC6F991FCD6F96F" box="[835,849,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">d</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFCFFF991FC0FF96F" box="[890,904,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">h</emphasis>
as listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFB9EF991FB59F96F" author="Salvadori, T." box="[1051,1246,1639,1665]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
. Salvadori noted that the 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFF74F97DFF78F94B" box="[241,255,1675,1701]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">h</emphasis>
specimen either must be a female or perhaps a young male, while specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFBDCF97DFBE0F94B" box="[1113,1127,1675,1701]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">d</emphasis>
was recorded as a male. As specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFE82F959FE92F927" box="[263,277,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">h</emphasis>
has been confirmed to be one of 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176321FFDBFD03F959FCB7F927" box="[646,816,1711,1737]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
currently found in MSNG in Genoa (C.E. 11302, based on its original label; Enrico Borgo, pers. comm.), and the NHMO specimen clearly is an adult male (head and back shiny black; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFEA3F901FE40F8FF" author="Gregory, P." box="[294,455,1783,1809]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refId="ref14736" refString="Gregory, P. (2020) Black Berrypecker (Melanocharis nigra). Version 1.0. Cornell Lab of Ornithology, Ithaca, New York. Available from: https: // doi. org / 10.2173 / bow. blaber 1.01 (accessed 19 January 2022)" type="book" year="2020">Gregory 2020</bibRefCitation>
), the latter must be concluded to be specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFC49F901FC5DF8FF" box="[972,986,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">d</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6321FFDBFF42F8EDFF72F807" blockId="16.[151,1437,1279,2025]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
Of the 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176321FFDBFE9DF8EDFE49F8DB" box="[280,462,1819,1845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFE53F8EDFD26F8D8" author="Salvadori, T." box="[470,673,1819,1846]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" pagination="896 - 976" refId="ref16237" refString="Salvadori, T. (1876 a) Descrizione di cinquantotto nuove specie di uccelli, ed osservazioni intorno ad altre poco note, della Nuova Guinea e di altre Isole Papuane, raccolte dal D. r Odoardo Beccari e dai cacciatori del Sig. A. A. Bruijn. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 896 - 976. [1875]" type="journal article" year="1876">Salvadori (1876a)</bibRefCitation>
based his description on, 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176321FFDBFC49F8EDFBE2F8DB" box="[972,1125,1819,1845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
(C.E. 11300–11303) are in MSNG in Genoa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFEE1F8C9FDCEF8B7" author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[356,585,1855,1881]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFE48F8B6FD81F8B7" box="[461,518,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">et al.</emphasis>
1979
</bibRefCitation>
). While 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFD23F8C9FC10F8B7" author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[678,919,1855,1881]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFC88F8B6FCC1F8B7" box="[781,838,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">et al.</emphasis>
(1979)
</bibRefCitation>
did not specify which specimens in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFAB4F8C9FF65F893" author="Salvadori, T." pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
these corresponded to, it has been confirmed by Enrico Borgo at the MSNG that their original labels indicate that they correspond to specimens 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFD9FF87EFDAFF84F" box="[538,552,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFDB3F87EFDC5F84F" box="[566,578,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">c</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFDD4F87EFDD8F84F" box="[593,607,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">g</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFD10F871FD24F84F" box="[661,675,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">h</emphasis>
. Another two (MZUT Av3953 and MZUT Av3954) are in MRSN in Turin (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFF61F85DFE40F82B" author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[228,455,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFECCF85AFE05F82B" box="[329,386,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
); these are specimens 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFD47F85DFD57F82B" box="[706,720,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">b</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6321FFDBFC8DF85DFC97F82B" box="[776,784,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">f</emphasis>
, respectively, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6321FFDBFC55F85DFB09F82B" author="Salvadori, T." box="[976,1166,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
(Giorgio Aimassi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6320FFDAFF42FF61FCA1FD1F" blockId="17.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFF42FF61FE70FF5F" author="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; Harrison, C. J. O." box="[199,503,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refId="ref16946" refString="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; Harrison, C. J. O. (1971) Type-specimens of birds in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. 2. Passerines. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 628 pp." type="book" year="1971">Warren &amp; Harrison (1971)</bibRefCitation>
also list 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176320FFDAFDE7FF61FD6CFF5F" box="[610,747,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in the BMNH (currently NHMUK 1858.3.10.143), an adult male collected by A.R. Wallace in the Aru Islands. This specimen was not among the eight that Salvadori based his description directly on, as all of those were collected by Beccari (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFCF5FF29FBAAFF17" author="Salvadori, T." box="[880,1069,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="983 - 990" refId="ref16308" refString="Salvadori, T. (1876 b) Descrizione di sei nuove specie di Uccelli delle Molucche, delle Kei e delle Aru e del maschio della Pachycephala lineolata, Wall. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 983 - 990. [1875]" type="journal article" year="1876">Salvadori 1876b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFBBDFF29FBF3FF17" author="Salvadori, T." box="[1080,1140,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">1881</bibRefCitation>
). However, Salvadori stated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFF6CFEF5FE16FEF3" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[233,401,259,285]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFF6CFEF5FE16FEF3" box="[233,401,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
replaces the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFDA6FEF5FD03FEF2" baseAuthorityName="Lesson" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[547,644,259,284]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFDA6FEF5FD03FEF2" box="[547,644,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of New 
<collectingCountry id="F34D760E6320FFDAFD61FEF5FCB2FEF3" box="[740,821,259,285]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Guinea</collectingCountry>
in the Aru Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFB8AFEF5FB4BFEF0" author="Salvadori, T." box="[1039,1228,259,286]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="983 - 990" refId="ref16308" refString="Salvadori, T. (1876 b) Descrizione di sei nuove specie di Uccelli delle Molucche, delle Kei e delle Aru e del maschio della Pachycephala lineolata, Wall. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 983 - 990. [1875]" type="journal article" year="1876">Salvadori 1876b</bibRefCitation>
), referring to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFAE1FEF5FF63FEAF" author="Gray, G. R." pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="169 - 198" refId="ref14426" refString="Gray, G. R. (1858) A list of the birds, with descriptions of new species obtained by Mr. Alfred R. Wallace in the Aru and Ke Islands. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 26, 169 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1858. tb 06363. x" type="journal article" year="1858">Gray (1858)</bibRefCitation>
, who mentioned 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176320FFDAFE22FED1FDC9FEAF" box="[423,590,295,321]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
from the Aru Islands, a male and a female collected by Wallace. Although these were listed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFEFEFEBDFDCEFE8A" box="[379,585,331,357]" class="Aves" family="Dicaeidae" genus="Prionichilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFEFEFEBDFDCEFE8A" box="[379,585,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Prionichilus niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFDEAFEBDFD7EFE8B" author="Gray, G. R." box="[623,761,330,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="169 - 198" refId="ref14426" refString="Gray, G. R. (1858) A list of the birds, with descriptions of new species obtained by Mr. Alfred R. Wallace in the Aru and Ke Islands. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 26, 169 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1858. tb 06363. x" type="journal article" year="1858">Gray (1858)</bibRefCitation>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFC8EFEBDFC5FFE8A" box="[779,984,331,357]" class="Aves" family="Dicaeidae" genus="Prionichilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFC8EFEBDFC5FFE8A" box="[779,984,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Prionichilus niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFC7DFEBDFBDBFE8A" baseAuthorityName="Lesson" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1016,1116,331,356]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFC7DFEBDFBDBFE8A" box="[1016,1116,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Salvadori assumed that he had just overlooked the differences separating 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFD22FE99FCD6FE67" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[679,849,367,393]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFD22FE99FCD6FE67" box="[679,849,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFC12FE99FC7CFE66" baseAuthorityName="Lesson" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[919,1019,367,392]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFC12FE99FC7CFE66" box="[919,1019,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and by doing so suggested that also these specimens were to be considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6320FFDAFDC2FE65FD69FE43" authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[583,750,403,429]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFDC2FE65FD69FE43" box="[583,750,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">M. chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male NHMUK 1858.3.10.143 is one of these specimens, while the female was recently discovered to also be present in the NHMUK collection (NHMUK 1858.3.10.139), together with yet another male (NHMUK 1873.5.12.1052). The latter male arrived in the collection from Wallace in 1873, when he sold his private collection of birds to the museum (Hein van Grouw, pers. comm.). Both of the specimens mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFEF0FDD5FE7AFDD3" author="Gray, G. R." box="[373,509,546,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="169 - 198" refId="ref14426" refString="Gray, G. R. (1858) A list of the birds, with descriptions of new species obtained by Mr. Alfred R. Wallace in the Aru and Ke Islands. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 26, 169 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1858. tb 06363. x" type="journal article" year="1858">Gray (1858)</bibRefCitation>
are consequently mentioned in the original description. Further, both the previously known male (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFEABFDB1FDC0FD8F" author="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; Harrison, C. J. O." box="[302,583,583,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refId="ref16946" refString="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; Harrison, C. J. O. (1971) Type-specimens of birds in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. 2. Passerines. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 628 pp." type="book" year="1971">Warren &amp; Harrison 1971</bibRefCitation>
) and the two recently discovered specimens (Hein van Grouw, pers. comm.) have labels in Salvadori’s handwriting, and also have 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6320FFDAFD6DFD9DFCC9FD6B" box="[744,846,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">‘co-type’</emphasis>
written on them. It, therefore, seems safe to conclude that Salvadori must have seen all three of these specimens. Based on this reasoning, and in accordance with Article 72.4.1.1 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6320FFDAFE0FFD45FBBCFD23" author="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[394,1083,691,717]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refId="ref14975" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999</bibRefCitation>
), the three NHMUK specimens should probably also be considered 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6320FFDAFDACFD21FD0CFD1F" box="[553,651,727,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">syntypes</typeStatus>
of this taxon.
</paragraph>
